author: ShadMOrdre

author: ShadMOrdre
notes: Revision 6 of lib_materials and lib_ecology, also known as v5.0. Contains almost everything from those revisions. Some material of little value has been omitted. Code for modifying terrain (e.g. producing lakes) has also been omitted. The remix is not suitable for survival mode (see the notes for more details)

author: ShadMOrdre
notes: Revision 11 of lib_materials and lib_ecology, also known as v5.02. Contains almost everything from those revisions. Some material of little value has been omitted. Code for modifying terrain (e.g. producing lakes) has also been omitted. The remix is not suitable for survival mode (see the notes for more details)

author: GreenDimond
notes: GreedDimond's fork. Imported everything except awards. Cobalt, osmium, platinum and titanium have been renamed as fictional sybilline, ozymandium, planexium and tritonium to avoid clashing with any code that wants the real-life metals

author: Gael-de-Sailly
notes: Imported the fir tree and mud node only. Did not import biomes, decorations (except for the fir tree) or ores. (The biomes are actually available in a CSV file that is not loaded, by default. See the notes in the remix's _biomes.csv)

author: D00Med

Because many farlands mods share a name with minetest_game mods, everything has been grouped into a hypothetical "farlands" mod. Original names for items are only specified in code when their mods don't appear in minetest_game (e.g. decoblocks, mapgen, etc)

author: Vanessa Ezekowitz
notes: Imported everything, but some code has been simplified. Coconuts and dates do not regrow, and date palm trees are not pollinated. Raw coconuts have been merged with coconut slices from ethereal-ng. Calls to biome_lib have been crudely emulated by Minetest decorations, so trees will not spawn in the same positions/quantities. Coconuts can only be cut with cutting boards

author: Wuzzy
notes: Imported everything except the duplicate ice bricks, and the special textures for stairs/slabs

author: Napiophelios
notes: Imported decorative items and compatibility with mesecons, but no furniture

author: PilzAdam
notes: PilzAdam's nether mod. The "override_nether_portal" package creates a portal using unilib obsidian/mese, but nothing else has been imported. Compatible with unilib's implementation of armour and staff of light

author: StarNinjas et al
notes: Imported everything, creating two separate compasses pointing at origin and spawn

author: npx
notes: Imported all mushrooms, fungi and truffles, but their behaviour has been changed to drastically improve the player experience (removing most ABMs). Mushrooms/funig growing on the ground now behave like minetest_game mushrooms (i.e. they are spreadable). Other mushrooms/fungi tend to grow on trees, and are not spreadable or placeable. Truffles can be found growing at the base of some trees, just below the surface. Spores have not been imported at all

author: Donald Trump et al
notes: Imported the flag printer and flag generation code. Did not import any of the mod's flags, instead created a new set of flags using textures from Wikipedia

author: Wuzzy
notes: Imported everything. Minetest settings controlling the position of the HUD have not been imported
